      "message": "You\u0027re right. In my experience, the big win is when you have private constructors and public Make functions that return unique_ptrs. e.g.:\n\n    static std::unique_ptr\u003cGrFragmentProcessor\u003e Make(SkPMColor4f color) {\n        return SkWrapUnique(new GrConstColorProcessor(color));\n    }\n\n(Replacing std::unique_ptr\u003cGrFragmentProcessor\u003e)\n\nI googled this for examples and actually realized there\u0027s a TOTW about it that I hadn\u0027t seen before: https://abseil.io/tips/134",
      "parentUuid": "e42428c9_e0a13589",
