      "message": "I think I don\u0027t see a big win.  This is the alternative right?\n\n    static std::unique_ptr\u003cGrFragmentProcessor\u003e Make(SkPMColor4f color) {\n        return std::unique_ptr\u003cGrFragmentProcessor\u003e{\n            new GrConstColorProcessor(color)\n        };\n    }\n\nIf it\u0027s a simple little inline factory in the header, we could also use this style to avoid typing type names redundantly,\n\n    static auto Make(SkPMColor4f color) {\n        return std::unique_ptr\u003cGrFragmentProcessor\u003e{\n            new GrConstColorProcessor(color)\n        };\n    }\n\nthough if the factory really is that simple, it might make sense to just make the constructor public and use std::make_unique.",
